{% block content %}

<!-- TOP OF PAGE -->

<div id="page-top"></div>

    <div id="section-id-page" class="container-fluid banner site-text">
        <h2 class="nom-de-page" style="padding-top:25px; text-align: center">Notre équipe</h2>
        <h3 style="text-align: center">L'équipe pédagogique</h3>
        <p class="page-location" style="padding-top:15px">
            <a href="equipe_pedagogique"> Equipe pédagogique | </a>
            <a href="comite_scientifique">Comité scientifique du programme | </a>
            <a href="comite_pilotage"> Comité de pilotage du projet | </a>
            <a href="equipe_projet"> Equipe du projet</a>
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="container site-text" style="padding-top: 30px">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-9 col-md-offset-3">
                <h3 class="orange">Equipe pédagogique</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/ooms.jpg') }}" height="200" width="auto" alt="ooms.jpg" title="Photo de Frédéric Ooms">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Frédéric Ooms</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Frederic Ooms holds a PhD in Chemistry from the Facultés Universitaires Notre-Dame de la Paix. Frédéric has published several peer-reviewed articles and patents. He
                was trained at Postdam D.School in design thinking, Berkley university (Lean Launch Pad By Steve Blank) and how to use the Business Model Canvas (Paris by Alex Osterwalder).
                He holds an MBA from Solvay Business School, where he teaches different classes in entrepreneurship and design thinking. His expertise covers both sciences and business
                aspects, applied to the real world of entrepreneurship.</br>
                He is executive director at ID Campus and the coordinator of PLUG-R Liege's creative hub. ID CAMPUS helps people, companies and organization to develop their creative
                muscles to foster creative economy and design better solutions for tomorrow's world.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/guilmot.jpg') }}" height="200" width="135" alt="guilmot.jpg" title="Photo de Nathalie Guilmot">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Nathalie Guilmot</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Nathalie Guilmot est titulaire d’un doctorat en sciences économiques et de gestion de l’Université Catholique de Louvain.</br>
                Assistante d’enseignement et de recherche au sein de la Louvain School of Management, ses activités d’enseignement portent principalement sur la stratégie d’entreprise,
                tandis que ses travaux de recherche sont orientés vers la gestion des changements organisationnels et l’évolution des rôles des managers intermédiaires.</br>
                Ses recherches ont été présentées lors de diverses conférences académiques et ont fait l’objet de plusieurs publications.  Elle est également membre du CRECIS (Center for
                Research in Entrepreneurial Change and Innovative Strategies).</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/delahaut.jpg') }}" height="200" width="auto" alt="delahaut.jpg" title="Photo de Fabian Delahaut">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Fabian Delahaut</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">MBA de la Solvay Brussels School, Licencié en philosophie de l’ULB, Executive Master en Management & Philosophies, Maître Praticien en PNL, comédien formé au Cours
                Florent, chargé de cours à la Solvay Brussels School, auteur du livre «Le crime de l’orateur – Prise de parole en public : 3 secrets et 60 techniques», aux Editions De Boeck.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/noterdaeme.jpg') }}" height="200" width="auto" alt="noterdaeme.jpg" title="Photo de Jan Noterdaeme">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Jan Noterdaeme</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Noterdaeme has a Master’s Degree in Law. He is co-author of the “Manifeste des Jeunes pour l’Europe”, and the co-founder of CSR Europe (1996), a Network of 100 corporate
                members and National Partner Organisations engaging 10.000 enterprises across Europe on Corporate Social Responsibility.</br>
                As from 1997 Jan played a leading role in the establishment by business leaders and deans and teachers of what became in 2002 the <strong>European Academy of Business in Society</strong>
                 (ABIS).</br>
                Since March 2007, he is also Maître de Conférence at the Catholic University of Louvain. where he co-founded with Professor Valérie Swaen the <strong>Louvain CSR Network</strong>.
                Since 2010, Jan is chairing the Stakeholder Jury of the <strong>Philippe de Woot International Inter-University Award on CSR</strong>. On behalf of the European C’homme’Pany Jan now also acts as Senior Advisor - External Relations for CSR Europe.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/calicis.png') }}" alt="calicis.png" title="Photo de Benoît Calicis">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Benoît Calicis</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Benoit Calicis holds a Commercial Engineering degree from the Louvain School of Management (Belgium) and a Master in Tax from the Catholic University of
                    Leuven (Belgium).</br>
                    He is Managing Partner in MEGA Learning, specialises in experiential learning through business simulation where he integrates his experience in Corporate Strategy,
                    Finance and Entrepreneurship and his passion for Strategic Games. He organises and develops business simulation workshops for multinational companies and top business
                    schools throughout Europe, the USA, Latin America and Asia.
                    Since 1998, he has developed and facilitated executive development programmes for more than 5000 managers from global corporations (Akzo Nobel, British Telecom,
                    China Telecom, France Telecom,…). Together with the MEGA Learning team, Benoit has developed more than 20 innovative business simulations in collaboration with
                    International Companies and Business Schools (“The 21st Century Car Challenge” with ESCP Europe and Renault, “Human Capital Challenge” with HEC Paris, “The Mobile
                    Phone Challenge” with Nokia, “Banksquare” with Nordea Bank,…). Benoit lectures in many business schools, in programmes in ESCP Europe in Paris, Madrid, Berlin and
                    London, in HEC Paris, INSEAD, IDRAC Lyon, Westminster Business Schools in,London, INPT in Casablanca
                    He also manages MEGA Learning key accounts and develops and supports its business partner’s network.</br>
                    Before joining MEGA Learning Benoit has worked as a tax consultant for Arthur Andersen, Brussels, where he has gained broad experience in international finance,
                    tax audit and planning, from large multinationals to local small and medium enterprises (SME).</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/baeyens.png') }}" alt="baeyens.jpg" title="Photo de Jean-Pierre Baeyens">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Jean-Pierre Baeyens</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Jean-Pierre Baeyens est <strong>Ingénieur Commercial de l'Ecole de Commerce Solvay</strong> (ULB - 1975) et <strong>Master of Business Administration de
                    l'Université d'Harvard</strong> (Harvard Business School 1979). Il est Chargé de Cours à l'Université Libre de Bruxelles où il est titulaire de la Chaire de
                    Marketing de la Solvay Brussels School of Economics & Management. Il assure également des programmes de formation et coaching en entreprise. Ses domaines de
                    spécialité sont la stratégie et la gouvernance des entreprises et organisations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row" style="padding-top: 25px">
            <div class="col-md-3">
                <img src="{{ asset('uploads/custom/images/dezanet.jpg') }}" alt="dezanet.png" title="Photo de Fabrice De Zanet">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-9">
                <h4 class="mauve">Fabrice De Zanet</h4>
                <p style="text-align: justify">Fabrice De Zanet est Professeur Assistant à HEC Liège. Licencié en psychologie du travail (ULg) et Docteur en sciences de gestion (HEC Liège), ses travaux
                    portent sur les questions de leadership, de culture, et de coopération au sein des organisations. Il s’intéresse au rôle de la confiance comme mécanisme de
                    coordination et de motivation au sein des organisations.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

